<para>
  Blur the given <varname>image</varname>.  This can be a useful way
  of reducing noise, at the obvious expense of a loss of resolution.
  The image is convolved with a Gaussian operator whose standard
  deviation is <varname>sigma</varname>.
</para>
<para>
  The <varname>radius</varname> parameter is the size of the mask used
  to perform the convolution, in pixels.  The new value of a pixel is
  the Gaussian weighted average of the pixel values in a
  <emphasis>square</emphasis> with sides of length <code>2*radius +
  1</code> in pixel units, centered on the pixel.
</para>
<para>
  In a color image, each RGB channel is blurred separately.
</para>
<para>
  This routine uses <ulink
  url="https://scikit-image.org/docs/stable/api/skimage.filters.html#skimage.filters.gaussian"
  role="external"><code>skimage.filters.gaussian</code></ulink> from
  the &skimage; library.
</para>
